doctype html
html
    head
        title URL Shortener Microservice
        link(href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Open+Sans" rel="stylesheet" )
        link(rel="stylesheet",type="text/css",href="/style.css")
        link(link rel="stylesheet" href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.2.1/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-GJzZqFGwb1QTTN6wy59ffF1BuGJpLSa9DkKMp0DgiMDm4iYMj70gZWKYbI706tWS" crossorigin="anonymous")
body.container
    h1 API Project: URL Shortener Microservice
    h2 User Story: 

    div
        |   I can POST a URL to [project_url]/api/shorturl/new and I will receive a shortened URL in the JSON response.
        |   Example : {"original_url":"www.google.com","short_url":1}
        br 
        br
        |   pass an invalid URL that doesn't follow the http(s)://www.example.com(/more/routes) format, the JSON response will 
        |   contain an error like {"error":"invalid URL"}: to be sure that the submitted url points to a valid site you can use the function dns.lookup(host, cb) from the dns core module.
        |   When I visit the shortened URL, it will redirect me to my original link.
    br
    
    h2 Short URL Creation
    br
    form(method="POST",action="/api/shorturl/new")
        .form-group
            label URL to be shortened:
            input.form-control(name="url",type="text",placeholder="example:www.google.com")
            br
            input.btn.btn-primary(type="submit" value="Post URL")


